President Obama spoke with UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon to discuss the need for greater international assistance in containing the Ebola outbreak in West Africa. The President thanked the Secretary-General for the United Nations' efforts in coordinating the global response and pledged additional US assistance. They also discussed the need for a broad coalition to counter ISIL and provide humanitarian aid in Iraq. The leaders talked about the importance of monitoring the cease-fire in eastern Ukraine and reviewed goals for the upcoming United Nations General Assembly, including the Secretary-General's Climate Summit and a Security Council session on foreign terrorist fighters chaired by the President.